> Named after Korea's most well-known BBQ dish, bulgogi sauce has a sweet and smoky
> flavour, thanks to its mix of soy, garlic, brown sugar and pear & apple purees.
> Bulgogi is a perfect match for rice and noodle dishes or even as a flavour driver in
> tacos.

> A popular condiment in many Asian countries, sambal paste's vibrant heat is perfect
> for boosting flavour in our Asian style dishes. This paste contains herbs and
> spices such as red chillies, lemongrass and tamarind, making it the perfect flavour
> driver for both veggie and meat dishes alike.

Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting
#lid{}.

Stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once
boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the #pot{} from the heat (still covered)
and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice
will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, trim and peel the @Carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons
down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @Rice Vinegar{15%ml}, @Sugar{1/2%tsp} for the
pickle and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Add the carrot ribbons, toss to coat, then set aside to pickle.

Halve the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g} widthways. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1}
(or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once
hot, add the Tenderstem® Broccoli and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}, then add a splash of
@water{splash}. Cover with a lid (or foil) and allow to cook until tender,
~{4-6%minutes} more. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Transfer to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, drain the @King Prawns{225%g}.

In a medium bowl, combine the @Indonesian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @Plain Flour{1%tbsp}
and @Salt{1/4%tsp}. Add the prawns and toss to coat.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in the (now empty) frying pan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, fry the prawns until golden and crispy, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns. Cook so they're
> opaque in the middle.

When the prawns are crispy, pour in the @Bulgogi Sauce{150%g}, @Sambal Paste{15%g}
(add less if you'd prefer things milder), half the @Soy Sauce{7.5%ml} and the
@Water for the Sauce{50%ml}.

Stir to combine, bring to the boil and simmer until thickened slightly,
~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the remaining
@Soy Sauce{7.5%ml}.

Share the rice between your bowls.

Top with the bulgogi prawns, garlic broccoli and pickled carrot in separate sections.

Enjoy!